# =============================================================================
# PAYMENT GATEWAY CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Payment gateways are configured through the database via the Super Admin panel.
# The configuration below documents the environment-level settings that can be used.
# In production, configure these settings via the payment gateway settings in the admin panel.
#
# IMPORTANT PRODUCTION SETTINGS:
# ⚠️  Set test_mode=false in the payment gateway settings for production
# ⚠️  Configure webhook secrets for secure webhook verification
# ⚠️  Use production API credentials (not sandbox credentials)
# ⚠️  Test signature verification in staging before deploying to production

# bKash Payment Gateway (Bangladesh)
# Required fields in gateway configuration (stored in database):
# - app_key: Your bKash App Key
# - app_secret: Your bKash App Secret
# - username: Your bKash API Username
# - password: Your bKash API Password
# - webhook_secret: Secret key for webhook signature verification (REQUIRED for production)
# - test_mode: Set to false for production, true for sandbox
#
# Production Base URL: https://tokenized.pay.bkash.com
# Sandbox Base URL: https://tokenized.sandbox.bkash.com
# API Documentation: https://developer.bkash.com/

# Nagad Payment Gateway (Bangladesh)
# Required fields in gateway configuration (stored in database):
# - merchant_id: Your Nagad Merchant ID
# - merchant_number: Your Nagad Merchant Number
# - merchant_private_key: Your RSA private key in PEM format
# - nagad_public_key: Nagad's RSA public key in PEM format
# - webhook_secret: Secret key for webhook signature verification (REQUIRED for production)
# - test_mode: Set to false for production, true for sandbox
#
# Production Base URL: https://api.mynagad.com
# Sandbox Base URL: https://sandbox.mynagad.com:8094
# API Documentation: https://developer.nagad.com.bd/

# SSLCommerz Payment Gateway (Bangladesh)
# Required fields in gateway configuration (stored in database):
# - store_id: Your SSLCommerz Store ID
# - store_password: Your SSLCommerz Store Password
# - webhook_secret: Secret key for webhook verification (Optional, uses verify_sign from SSLCommerz)
# - test_mode: Set to false for production, true for sandbox
# - currency: Currency code (default: BDT)
#
# Production Base URL: https://securepay.sslcommerz.com
# Sandbox Base URL: https://sandbox.sslcommerz.com
# API Documentation: https://developer.sslcommerz.com/

# Stripe Payment Gateway (International)
# Required fields in gateway configuration (stored in database):
# - secret_key: Your Stripe Live Secret Key (sk_live_...)
# - test_secret_key: Your Stripe Test Secret Key (sk_test_...) for testing
# - publishable_key: Your Stripe Live Publishable Key (pk_live_...)
# - test_publishable_key: Your Stripe Test Publishable Key (pk_test_...) for testing
# - webhook_secret: Webhook signing secret from Stripe Dashboard (whsec_...) (REQUIRED)
# - test_mode: Set to false for production, true for testing
# - currency: Currency code (default: usd)
#
# API Documentation: https://stripe.com/docs/api
#
# To get webhook signing secret:
# 1. Go to Stripe Dashboard > Developers > Webhooks
# 2. Add endpoint: https://yourdomain.com/webhooks/payment/stripe
# 3. Copy the signing secret (starts with whsec_)

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES FOR PAYMENT GATEWAYS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Always use webhook signature verification in production
# 2. Never commit real API credentials to version control
# 3. Rotate webhook secrets periodically
# 4. Monitor failed webhook verifications as they may indicate attacks
# 5. Test all payment flows in staging before production deployment
# 6. Keep gateway credentials encrypted in the database
# 7. Use separate credentials for each environment (dev/staging/production)

